node.text:
https://smittenkitchen.com/2007/10/butternut-squash-and-caramelized-onion-galette/

Did you miss my IG Live demo of making smittenkitchen.com's butternut squash and caramelized onion galette on Friday, 11/8? Good news! We finally figured out how to share and save it forever on IGTV (thank you to everyone who DMed me with tips). Hope you make it, too! [Butternut Squash and Caramelized Onion Galette on smittenkitchen.com]

node.title: butternut squash and caramelized onion galette

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 06, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: A spectacularly September-ish pie with with apples, plums and an extra thick cookie-like lid comes together in very little time, even on a Monday afternoon. // Single-Crust Apple and Plum Pie on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Dry, beleaguered honey cake is no way to kick off 5782. This best-in-category classic from Marcy Goldman is the kind you make every year -- deeply spiced, great crumb, and very cozy. It gets better as it has time to rest, honestly, just like me. // Majestic and Moist Honey Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: f you’ve been felled by brisket recipes in the past that produced leaden, forgettable roasts, this recipe wants to be your brisket vindication -- tender, perfectly cooked, perfectly flavored every single time. And, it's even better on days two and three, should you be trying to get some cooking out of the way today. // Tangy Spiced Brisket on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 05, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Trying to figure out how to merge your Labor Day and super-early Jewish New Year agendas? Ropes of stretchy bread studded with apples, sweetened with honey, then glazed to a lacquered shine and baked into generous loaves turns out to be an excellent idea on a cloudy day, no matter what else is on your docket this weekend. Leftovers, should any survive today, make astoundingly good french toast my kids are already clamoring for. // Apple and Honey Challah on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 04, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Going somewhere this weekend? This is the cake you should take with you -- tall and perfectly-streuseled, this blueberry crumb cake from the late, great Maida Heatter is what late summer bliss looks like to me. // Blueberry Crumb Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 03, 2021. May be an image of powdered sugar.

node.text: Knots of barely sweetened doughnut strands absolutely blizzarded with powdered sugar are my favorite thing to eat on a beach boardwalk. It turns out it also takes barely 15 minutes to make at home and tastes exactly as good as you remember it. // Funnel Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it. ‬

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 02, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Far from the usual mayo-slicked bowls of suspicion and dread, this pasta salad has grilled vegetables, a vinaigrette so good, you'll want to eat from a spoon, and is designed to be eaten on laps, sitting outside -- hooray. I hope everyone is safe, warm, and dry right now; we are out of town but know that NY had a rough night. Here's to a brighter weekend ahead. // Charred Eggplant and Walnut Pesto Pasta Salad on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on September 01, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Everything great about summer produce -- burst cherry tomatoes, quick sautéed zucchini, sweet crunchy corn, freshly dug scallions -- folded into one immensely flaky rustic parmesan-flecked crust. This dish is a forever SK favorite. // Burst Tomato Galette with Corn and Zucchini on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on August 31, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Marian Burros's 1983 plum torte is an 8-ingredient, 4-step cult classic in which a mass of plums are coated with cinnamon sugar and baked into a pancake-like batter, where they melt into pie-like pockets and you definitely don't want to miss it. We make it every summer, usually twice. // Purple Plum Torte on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on August 30, 2021. May be an image of succotash.

node.text: Corn chowder, reimagined as a salad, from only six ingredients and using a single pan. Obviously, this is exactly what we have to cook next. // Corn Chowder Salad on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by smitten kitchen on August 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, fruit and dessert.

node.text: A dead-simple pastry cream you can use as a foundation for something more elaborate or, as we do here, a tiny cup of pudding. The roasted blueberries are really here to show off. // Vanilla Custards with Roasted Blueberries on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: A forever summer favorite, you do not need one fancy thing to make this, save the freshest clams you can find. You can pick them up on the way home from wherever you’ve been today, knowing that cooking dinner will be the easiest part of it. // Linguine and Clams on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile.
